snSwIfFastSpanPortEnable.name: snSwIfFastSpanPortEnable
snSwIfFastSpanPortEnable.description: The enabled/disabled fast span port status of the port.

snSwIfFastSpanUplinkEnable.name: snSwIfFastSpanUplinkEnable
snSwIfFastSpanUplinkEnable.description: The enabled/disabled fast span uplink status of the port.

snSwIfVlanId.name: snSwIfVlanId
snSwIfVlanId.description: The ID of a VLAN of which this port is a member. Port must be untagged. For tagged port which belongs to multiple VLANs, this object return 0 which is an invalid VLAN ID value, reading is valid only for untagged and dual mode, writing is valid for only dual mode.

snSwIfRouteOnly.name: snSwIfRouteOnly
snSwIfRouteOnly.description: Enable/Disable L2 switching of a routing switch port. By default, the routing switch performs routing first. If routing failed, it performs switching. Enable route only instrcuts the routing switch to perform routing only. For a L2 switching only product, reading this object always return 'disabled', writing 'enabled' to this object takes no effect.

snSwIfPresent.name: snSwIfPresent
snSwIfPresent.description: Indicate if the port is absent or present. This object only valid for M4 module.

snSwIfGBICStatus.name: snSwIfGBICStatus
snSwIfGBICStatus.description: Indicate if the gig port has GBICs on them. If set to GBIC(1), it means that the port is GBIC. If set to miniGBIC(2), it means that the port miniGBIC. If set to empty(3), it means that the GBIC is missing. Value other(4) means that the port not a removable gig port.

snSwIfLoadInterval.name: snSwIfLoadInterval
snSwIfLoadInterval.description: The time in seconds for which average port utilization should be carried out. The value should be incremental of 30 seconds, between the ranges specified.

snSwIfStatsInFrames.name: snSwIfStatsInFrames
snSwIfStatsInFrames.description: The total number of packets received on the interface.

snSwIfStatsOutFrames.name: snSwIfStatsOutFrames
snSwIfStatsOutFrames.description: The total number of packets transmitted out of the interface.

snSwIfStatsAlignErrors.name: snSwIfStatsAlignErrors
snSwIfStatsAlignErrors.description: dot3StatsAlignmentErrors : A count of frames received on a particular interface that are not an integral number of octets in length and do not pass the FCS check. The count represented by an instance of this object is incremented when the alignmentError status is returned by the MAC service to the LLC (or other MAC user). Received frames for which multiple error conditions obtain are, according to the conventions of IEEE 802.3 Layer Management, counted exclusively according to the error status presented to the LLC.

snSwIfStatsFCSErrors.name: snSwIfStatsFCSErrors
snSwIfStatsFCSErrors.description: dot3StatsFCSErrors : A count of frames received on a particular interface that are an integral number of octets in length but do not pass the FCS check. The count represented by an instance of this object is incremented when the frameCheckError status is returned by the MAC service to the LLC (or other MAC user). Received frames for which multiple error conditions obtain are, according to the conventions of IEEE 802.3 Layer Management, counted exclusively according to the error status presented to the LLC.

snSwIfStatsMultiColliFrames.name: snSwIfStatsMultiColliFrames
snSwIfStatsMultiColliFrames.description: dot3StatsMultipleCollisionFrames : A count of successfully transmitted frames on a particular interface for which transmission is inhibited by more than one collision. A frame that is counted by an instance of this object is also counted by the corresponding instance of either the ifOutUcastPkts, ifOutMulticastPkts, or ifOutBroadcastPkts, and is not counted by the corresponding instance of the dot3StatsSingleCollisionFrames object.

snSwIfStatsTxColliFrames.name: snSwIfStatsTxColliFrames
snSwIfStatsTxColliFrames.description: A count of successfully transmitted frames on a particular interface for which transmission is inhibited by more than one collision. A frame that is counted by a combination of both dot3StatsSingleCollisionFrames and dot3StatsMultipleCollisionFrames objects.

snSwIfStatsRxColliFrames.name: snSwIfStatsRxColliFrames
snSwIfStatsRxColliFrames.description: A count of successfully received frames on a particular interface for which transmission is inhibited by more than one collision. This object is not specified in dot3 but it has the same functionarity as snSwIfStatsTxColliFrames.

snSwIfStatsFrameTooLongs.name: snSwIfStatsFrameTooLongs
snSwIfStatsFrameTooLongs.description: dot3StatsFrameTooLongs : A count of frames received on a particular interface that exceed the maximum permitted frame size. The count represented by an instance of this object is incremented when the frameTooLong status is returned by the MAC service to the LLC (or other MAC user). Received frames for which multiple error conditions obtain are, according to the conventions of IEEE 802.3 Layer Management, counted exclusively according to the error status presented to the LLC.

snSwIfStatsFrameTooShorts.name: snSwIfStatsFrameTooShorts
snSwIfStatsFrameTooShorts.description: A count of frames received on a particular interface that below the minimum permitted frame size.

snSwIfStatsInBcastFrames.name: snSwIfStatsInBcastFrames
snSwIfStatsInBcastFrames.description: The total number of broadcast packets received on the interface.

snSwIfStatsOutBcastFrames.name: snSwIfStatsOutBcastFrames
snSwIfStatsOutBcastFrames.description: The total number of broadcast packets transmitted out of the interface.

snSwIfStatsInMcastFrames.name: snSwIfStatsInMcastFrames
snSwIfStatsInMcastFrames.description: The total number of multicast packets received on the interface.

snSwIfStatsOutMcastFrames.name: snSwIfStatsOutMcastFrames
snSwIfStatsOutMcastFrames.description: The total number of multicast packets transmitted out of the interface.

snSwIfStatsInDiscard.name: snSwIfStatsInDiscard
snSwIfStatsInDiscard.description: The number of inbound packets which were chosen to be discarded even though no errors had been detected to prevent their being deliverable to a higher-layer protocol. One possible reason for discarding such a packet could be to free up buffer space.

snSwIfStatsOutDiscard.name: snSwIfStatsOutDiscard
snSwIfStatsOutDiscard.description: The number of outbound packets which were chosen to be discarded even though no errors had been detected to prevent their being transmitted. One possible reason for discarding such a packet could be to free up buffer space.

snSwIfStatsMacStations.name: snSwIfStatsMacStations
snSwIfStatsMacStations.description: The total number of MAC Stations connected to the interface.

snSwIfStatsLinkChange.name: snSwIfStatsLinkChange
snSwIfStatsLinkChange.description: The total number of link state change of the interface.

snSwIfInOctets.name: snSwIfInOctets
snSwIfInOctets.description: The total number of octets received on the interface, including framing characters. This object is a 64-bit counter of the ifInOctets object, defined in RFC 1213. The octet string is in big-endian byte order.

snSwIfOutOctets.name: snSwIfOutOctets
snSwIfOutOctets.description: The total number of octets transmitted out of the interface, including framing characters. This object is a 64-bit counter of the ifOutOctets object, defined in RFC 1213. The octet string is in big-endian byte order.

snSwIfStatsInBitsPerSec.name: snSwIfStatsInBitsPerSec
snSwIfStatsInBitsPerSec.description: The number of bits per second received on the interface over a 5 minutes interval.

snSwIfStatsOutBitsPerSec.name: snSwIfStatsOutBitsPerSec
snSwIfStatsOutBitsPerSec.description: The number of bits per second transmitted out of the interface over a 5 minutes interval.

snSwIfStatsInPktsPerSec.name: snSwIfStatsInPktsPerSec
snSwIfStatsInPktsPerSec.description: The number of packets per second received on the interface over a 5 minutes interval.

snSwIfStatsOutPktsPerSec.name: snSwIfStatsOutPktsPerSec
snSwIfStatsOutPktsPerSec.description: The number of packets per second transmitted out of the interface over a 5 minutes interval.

snSwIfStatsInUtilization.name: snSwIfStatsInUtilization
snSwIfStatsInUtilization.description: The input network utilization in hundredths of a percent over a 5 minutes interval.

snSwIfStatsOutUtilization.name: snSwIfStatsOutUtilization
snSwIfStatsOutUtilization.description: The output network utilization in hundredths of a percent over a 5 minutes interval.

snSwIfStatsInKiloBitsPerSec.name: snSwIfStatsInKiloBitsPerSec
snSwIfStatsInKiloBitsPerSec.description: Bit rate in kilobits per second received on the 10G and faster interface over a 5 minutes interval.

snSwIfStatsOutKiloBitsPerSec.name: snSwIfStatsOutKiloBitsPerSec
snSwIfStatsOutKiloBitsPerSec.description: Bit rate in kilobits per second transmitted out of the 10G and faster interface over a 5 minutes interval.

snSwIfStatsInJumboFrames.name: snSwIfStatsInJumboFrames
snSwIfStatsInJumboFrames.description: The total number of jumbo packets received on the interface.

snSwIfStatsOutJumboFrames.name: snSwIfStatsOutJumboFrames
snSwIfStatsOutJumboFrames.description: The total number of jumbo packets transmitted out of the interface.

snSwIfMacLearningDisable.name: snSwIfMacLearningDisable
snSwIfMacLearningDisable.description: The status of MAC learning feature on an ethernet port. For POS port, Get operation will return the default value and Set operation will return an error.

snSwIfInfoL2FowardEnable.name: snSwIfInfoL2FowardEnable
snSwIfInfoL2FowardEnable.description: The status of cluster L2 forward feature on an ethernet port. When this object is set to disable, the STP protocol packets coming on the MCT VLANs are dropped. The snSwIfInfoL2FowardEnable has more preference than brcdMctL2Forward for this interface when set with enable(1) or disable(2). When set to globalConfig(3) the status of brcdMctL2Forward object applies for this interface.

snSwIfInfoAllowAllVlan.name: snSwIfInfoAllowAllVlan
snSwIfInfoAllowAllVlan.description: Specifies allowing all vlan packets for pbr

snSwIfInfoNativeMacAddress.name: snSwIfInfoNativeMacAddress
snSwIfInfoNativeMacAddress.description: The port native MAC address. The native MAC address represents the switch port.

snIfOpticalMonitoringInfoTable.name: snIfOpticalMonitoringInfoTable
snIfOpticalMonitoringInfoTable.description: This table lists the instrumented parameters of all optical interfaces.

snIfOpticalMonitoringInfoEntry.name: snIfOpticalMonitoringInfoEntry
snIfOpticalMonitoringInfoEntry.description: Only the ifIndices of optical interfaces whose parameters need to be monitored will be used to index this table.

snIfOpticalMonitoringTemperature.name: snIfOpticalMonitoringTemperature
snIfOpticalMonitoringTemperature.description: This object holds the value of the transmitter laser diode temperature for the interface. This object indicates the health of the transmitter. The format is xxx.yyyy C(elcius), followed by whether the measured value is normal, high/low alarm or high/low warning. For 100G LR4 and LR10 optic, this returns the average temperature for all lanes.

snIfOpticalMonitoringTxPower.name: snIfOpticalMonitoringTxPower
snIfOpticalMonitoringTxPower.description: This object holds the value of the transmitter optical signal power for the interface, measured in dBm, followed by whether this is a normal value, or high/low warning or alarm. For 100G LR4 and LR10 optic, this returns the aggregated Tx Power for all lanes.

snIfOpticalMonitoringRxPower.name: snIfOpticalMonitoringRxPower
snIfOpticalMonitoringRxPower.description: This object holds the value of the receiver optical signal power for the interface, measured in dBm, followed by whether this is a normal value, or high/low warning or alarm. For 100G LR4 and LR10 optic, this returns the aggregated Rx Power for all lanes.

snIfOpticalMonitoringTxBiasCurrent.name: snIfOpticalMonitoringTxBiasCurrent
snIfOpticalMonitoringTxBiasCurrent.description: Tx Bias Current. It is measured in mA, and is followed by whether this is a normal value, or high/low warning or alarm. For 100G LR4 and LR10 optic, this returns the aggregated Tx Bias Current for all lanes.

snIfMediaInfoTable.name: snIfMediaInfoTable
snIfMediaInfoTable.description: This table lists the information of the media device (SFP/XFP/Copper) installed in the physical port. Only the ifIndices of Ethernet ports those are associated with the operational cards will be included in this table.

snIfMediaInfoEntry.name: snIfMediaInfoEntry
snIfMediaInfoEntry.description: An entry in the Interface Media Information table. The ifIndices of ethernet interfaces will be used to index this table.

snIfMediaType.name: snIfMediaType
snIfMediaType.description: The type of the media installed in the physical port.

snIfMediaVendorName.name: snIfMediaVendorName
snIfMediaVendorName.description: The media vendor name, full name of the corporation.

snIfMediaVersion.name: snIfMediaVersion
snIfMediaVersion.description: The media vendor product version number.

snIfMediaSerialNumber.name: snIfMediaSerialNumber
snIfMediaSerialNumber.description: The vendor serial number of the media device.

snIfOpticalLaneMonitoringTable.name: snIfOpticalLaneMonitoringTable
snIfOpticalLaneMonitoringTable.description: This table lists the instrumented parameters of all lanes within a 40G Optic of type SR4 and LR4, 100G optic of type LR4 and LR10. LR4 and SR4 have 4 lanes per optic, LR10 has 10 lanes per optic.

snIfOpticalLaneMonitoringEntry.name: snIfOpticalLaneMonitoringEntry
snIfOpticalLaneMonitoringEntry.description: Only the ifIndices of optical interfaces whose parameters need to be monitored will be used to index this table.

snIfOpticalLaneMonitoringLane.name: snIfOpticalLaneMonitoringLane
snIfOpticalLaneMonitoringLane.description: The lane number of this 40G or 100G optic. LR4 and SR4 have 4 lanes per optic. LR10 has 10 lanes per optic.

snIfOpticalLaneMonitoringTemperature.name: snIfOpticalLaneMonitoringTemperature
snIfOpticalLaneMonitoringTemperature.description: This object holds the value of the transmitter laser diode temperature for the lane in the interface. This object indicates the health of the transmitter. The format is xxx.yyyy C(elcius), followed by whether the measured value is normal, high/low alarm or high/low warning.

snIfOpticalLaneMonitoringTxPower.name: snIfOpticalLaneMonitoringTxPower
snIfOpticalLaneMonitoringTxPower.description: This object holds the value of the transmitter optical signal power for the lane in the interface, measured in dBm, followed by whether this is a normal value, or high/low warning or alarm.

snIfOpticalLaneMonitoringRxPower.name: snIfOpticalLaneMonitoringRxPower
snIfOpticalLaneMonitoringRxPower.description: This object holds the value of the receiver optical signal power for the lane in the interface, measured in dBm, followed by whether this is a normal value, or high/low warning or alarm.

snIfOpticalLaneMonitoringTxBiasCurrent.name: snIfOpticalLaneMonitoringTxBiasCurrent
snIfOpticalLaneMonitoringTxBiasCurrent.description: Tx Bias Current. It is measured in mA, and is followed by whether this is a normal value, or high/low warning or alarm.

brcdIfEgressCounterInfoTable.name: brcdIfEgressCounterInfoTable
brcdIfEgressCounterInfoTable.description: This table lists the information of egress counters of all the queues in the physical ports.

brcdIfEgressCounterInfoEntry.name: brcdIfEgressCounterInfoEntry
brcdIfEgressCounterInfoEntry.description: An entry in the Interface Egress Counter Information table. The ifIndices of ethernet interfaces and the queue number will be used to index this table.

brcdIfEgressCounterIfIndex.name: brcdIfEgressCounterIfIndex
brcdIfEgressCounterIfIndex.description: The port number of egress counter in the physical port. The port/interface index (ifindex).

brcdIfEgressCounterQueueId.name: brcdIfEgressCounterQueueId
brcdIfEgressCounterQueueId.description: The queue number of egress counter in the given port.

brcdIfEgressCounterType.name: brcdIfEgressCounterType
brcdIfEgressCounterType.description: The queue type of the egress counter in a given port.

brcdIfEgressCounterPkts.name: brcdIfEgressCounterPkts
brcdIfEgressCounterPkts.description: The egress packet counters of the queue in a given port.

brcdIfEgressCounterDropPkts.name: brcdIfEgressCounterDropPkts
brcdIfEgressCounterDropPkts.description: The egress dropped packet counters of the queue in a given port.

snFdbTable.name: snFdbTable
snFdbTable.description: This table contains snFdb information for each station known to the system, one entry per station.

snFdbEntry.name: snFdbEntry
snFdbEntry.description: Each entry represents the information of a static MAC station.

snFdbStationIndex.name: snFdbStationIndex
snFdbStationIndex.description: The FDB Station index to the Fdb Station Table.

snFdbStationAddr.name: snFdbStationAddr
snFdbStationAddr.description: The snFdbs physical address. The physical address represents a MAC Station.

snFdbStationPort.name: snFdbStationPort
snFdbStationPort.description: Station slot/port number. The bit 0 to bit 7: port number. The bit 8 to bit 11: slot number (slot for chassis only).

snFdbStationQos.name: snFdbStationQos
snFdbStationQos.description: The Stand alone stackable station Qos Priority values are: low(0) -- low prority high(1) -- high prority. The BigIron switch station Priority values are: level0(0), level1(1), level2(2), level3(3), level4(4), level5(5), level6(6), level7(7)

snFdbStationType.name: snFdbStationType
snFdbStationType.description: The station type values are: notSupported -- a read value only : this product does not support MultiLayer Switching. host -- any MAC station. router -- a router-typed station.

snFdbRowStatus.name: snFdbRowStatus
snFdbRowStatus.description: This object is used to create and delete row in the table and control if they are used. The values that can be written are: delete(3)...deletes the row create(4)...creates a new row If the row exists, then a SET with value of create(4) returns error 'badValue'. Deleted rows go away immediately. The following values can be returned on reads: noSuch(0)...no such row other(1)....some other case valid(2)....the row exists and is valid

snPortStpTable.name: snPortStpTable
snPortStpTable.description: A specific snPortStpTable consists of a number of switch ports. This table only exists if only if snVLanByPortCfgTable exists and snVLanByPortCfgStpMode is enabled for each VLAN.

snPortStpEntry.name: snPortStpEntry
snPortStpEntry.description: An entry in the snPortStpTable indicates the configuration on a specified port. A SNMP SET PDU for a row of the snPortStpTable requires the entired sequence of the MIB Objects in each snPortStpEntry stored in one PDU. Otherwise, GENERR return-value will be returned.

snPortStpVLanId.name: snPortStpVLanId
snPortStpVLanId.description: The VLAN ID of the VLAN switch community.

snPortStpPortNum.name: snPortStpPortNum
snPortStpPortNum.description: The port number of the Switch. The bit 0 to bit 7: port number. The bit 8 to bit 11: slot number (slot for chassis only).

snPortStpPortPriority.name: snPortStpPortPriority
snPortStpPortPriority.description: The value of the priority field which is contained in the first (in network byte order) octet of the (2 octet long) Port ID. The other octet of the Port ID is given by the value of dot1dStpPort.

snPortStpPathCost.name: snPortStpPathCost
snPortStpPathCost.description: dot1dStpPortPathCost : The contribution of this port to the path cost of paths towards the spanning tree root which include this port. 802.1D-1990 recommends that the default value of this parameter be in inverse proportion to the speed of the attached LAN. Writing value zero to this object sets path cost to a default value which automatically changes according to port speed. Reading value zero indicates an unknown path cost value because port speed cannot be determined due to speed auto sense in progress.

snPortStpOperState.name: snPortStpOperState
snPortStpOperState.description: By default, this mode is set to notActivated(0). notActivated(0)...the Port STP entry is not activated and not in running mode. activated(1)......the Port STP entry is activated and in running mode

snPortStpPortEnable.name: snPortStpPortEnable
snPortStpPortEnable.description: The enabled/disabled status of the port.

snPortStpPortForwardTransitions.name: snPortStpPortForwardTransitions
snPortStpPortForwardTransitions.description: The number of times this port has transitioned from the Learning state to the Forwarding state.

snPortStpPortState.name: snPortStpPortState
snPortStpPortState.description: The port's current state as defined by application of the Spanning Tree Protocol. This state controls what action a port takes on reception of a frame. If the bridge has detected a port that is malfunctioning it will place that port into the broken(6) state. For ports which are disabled (see dot1dStpPortEnable), this object will have a value of disabled(1).

snPortStpPortDesignatedCost.name: snPortStpPortDesignatedCost
snPortStpPortDesignatedCost.description: The path cost of the Designated Port of the segment connected to this port. This value is compared to the Root Path Cost field in received bridge PDUs.

snPortStpPortDesignatedRoot.name: snPortStpPortDesignatedRoot
snPortStpPortDesignatedRoot.description: The unique Bridge Identifier of the Bridge recorded as the Root in the Configuration BPDUs transmitted by the Designated Bridge for the segment to which the port is attached.

snPortStpPortDesignatedBridge.name: snPortStpPortDesignatedBridge
snPortStpPortDesignatedBridge.description: The Bridge Identifier of the bridge which this port considers to be the Designated Bridge for this port's segment.

snPortStpPortDesignatedPort.name: snPortStpPortDesignatedPort
snPortStpPortDesignatedPort.description: The Port Identifier of the port on the Designated Bridge for this port's segment.

snPortStpPortAdminRstp.name: snPortStpPortAdminRstp
snPortStpPortAdminRstp.description: Enable or disable RSTP of a port which is a member of a VLAN. If the VLAN is not operating in RSTP, this object will return FALSE(2) and this object is not writable.

snPortStpPortProtocolMigration.name: snPortStpPortProtocolMigration
snPortStpPortProtocolMigration.description: When operating in RSTP (version 2) mode, writing TRUE(1) to this object forces this port to transmit RSTP BPDUs. Any other operation on this object has no effect and it always returns FALSE(2) when read.

snPortStpPortAdminEdgePort.name: snPortStpPortAdminEdgePort
snPortStpPortAdminEdgePort.description: The administrative value of the Edge Port parameter. A value of TRUE(1) indicates that this port should be assumed as an edge-port and a value of FALSE(2) indicates that this port should be assumed as a non-edge-port.

snPortStpPortAdminPointToPoint.name: snPortStpPortAdminPointToPoint
snPortStpPortAdminPointToPoint.description: The administrative point-to-point status of the LAN segment attached to this port. A value of TRUE(1) indicates that this port should always be treated as if it is connected to a point-to-point link. A value of FALSE(2) indicates that this port should be treated as having a shared media connection.

snIfStpTable.name: snIfStpTable
snIfStpTable.description: A specific snIfStpTable consists of a number of switch ports. This table only exists if only if snVLanByPortCfgTable exists and snVLanByPortCfgStpMode is enabled for each VLAN.

snIfStpEntry.name: snIfStpEntry
snIfStpEntry.description: An entry in the snIfStpTable indicates the configuration on a specified port. A SNMP SET PDU for a row of the snIfStpTable requires the entired sequence of the MIB Objects in each snIfStpEntry stored in one PDU. Otherwise, GENERR return-value will be returned.

snIfStpVLanId.name: snIfStpVLanId
snIfStpVLanId.description: The VLAN ID of the VLAN switch community.

snIfStpPortNum.name: snIfStpPortNum
snIfStpPortNum.description: The port number of the Switch. It has the ifIndex value.

snIfStpPortPriority.name: snIfStpPortPriority
snIfStpPortPriority.description: The value of the priority field which is contained in the first (in network byte order) octet of the (2 octet long) Port ID. The other octet of the Port ID is given by the value of dot1dStpPort.

snIfStpCfgPathCost.name: snIfStpCfgPathCost
snIfStpCfgPathCost.description: dot1dStpPortPathCost : The contribution of this port to the path cost of paths towards the spanning tree root which include this port. 802.1D-1990 recommends that the default value of this parameter be in inverse proportion to the speed of the attached LAN. Writing value zero to this object sets path cost to a default value which automatically changes according to port speed.

snIfStpOperState.name: snIfStpOperState
snIfStpOperState.description: For FastIron: By default, this mode is set to notActivated(0). notActivated(0)...the Port STP or RSTP entry is not configured and not in running mode. activated(1)......the Port STP or RSTP entry is enabled. For NetIron: By default, this mode is set to notActivated(0). notActivated(0)...the Port STP entry is not activated and not in running mode. activated(1)......the Port STP entry is activated and in running mode

snIfStpPortState.name: snIfStpPortState
snIfStpPortState.description: The port's current state as defined by application of the Spanning Tree Protocol. This state controls what action a port takes on reception of a frame. If the bridge has detected a port that is malfunctioning it will place that port into the broken(6) state. For ports which are disabled (see dot1dStpPortEnable), this object will have a value of disabled(1).

snIfStpPortDesignatedCost.name: snIfStpPortDesignatedCost
snIfStpPortDesignatedCost.description: The path cost of the Designated Port of the segment connected to this port. This value is compared to the Root Path Cost field in received bridge PDUs.

snIfStpPortDesignatedRoot.name: snIfStpPortDesignatedRoot
snIfStpPortDesignatedRoot.description: The unique Bridge Identifier of the Bridge recorded as the Root in the Configuration BPDUs transmitted by the Designated Bridge for the segment to which the port is attached.

snIfStpPortDesignatedBridge.name: snIfStpPortDesignatedBridge
snIfStpPortDesignatedBridge.description: The Bridge Identifier of the bridge which this port considers to be the Designated Bridge for this port's segment.

snIfStpPortDesignatedPort.name: snIfStpPortDesignatedPort
snIfStpPortDesignatedPort.description: The Port Identifier of the port on the Designated Bridge for this port's segment.

snIfStpPortAdminRstp.name: snIfStpPortAdminRstp
snIfStpPortAdminRstp.description: Enable or disable RSTP of a port which is a member of a VLAN. If the VLAN is not operating in RSTP, this object will return FALSE(2) and this object is not writable.

snIfStpPortProtocolMigration.name: snIfStpPortProtocolMigration
snIfStpPortProtocolMigration.description: When operating in RSTP (version 2) mode, writing TRUE(1) to this object forces this port to transmit RSTP BPDUs. Any other operation on this object has no effect and it always returns FALSE(2) when read.

snIfStpPortAdminEdgePort.name: snIfStpPortAdminEdgePort
snIfStpPortAdminEdgePort.description: The administrative value of the Edge Port parameter. A value of TRUE(1) indicates that this port should be assumed as an edge-port and a value of FALSE(2) indicates that this port should be assumed as a non-edge-port.

snIfStpPortAdminPointToPoint.name: snIfStpPortAdminPointToPoint
snIfStpPortAdminPointToPoint.description: The administrative point-to-point status of the LAN segment attached to this port. A value of TRUE(1) indicates that this port should always be treated as if it is connected to a point-to-point link. A value of FALSE(2) indicates that this port should be treated as having a shared media connection.

snIfStpOperPathCost.name: snIfStpOperPathCost
snIfStpOperPathCost.description: dot1dStpPortPathCost : The contribution of this port to the path cost of paths towards the spanning tree root which include this port. 802.1D-1990 recommends that the default value of this parameter be in inverse proportion to the speed of the attached LAN. Reading value zero indicates an unknown path cost value because port speed cannot be determined due to speed auto sense in progress or port link is down.

snIfStpBPDUTransmitted.name: snIfStpBPDUTransmitted
snIfStpBPDUTransmitted.description: STP/RSTP bridge protocol unit transmitted counter.

snIfStpBPDUReceived.name: snIfStpBPDUReceived
snIfStpBPDUReceived.description: STP/RSTP bridge protocol unit received counter.

snIfRstpConfigBPDUReceived.name: snIfRstpConfigBPDUReceived
snIfRstpConfigBPDUReceived.description: RSTP configuration bridge protocol unit received counter.

snIfRstpTCNBPDUReceived.name: snIfRstpTCNBPDUReceived
snIfRstpTCNBPDUReceived.description: RSTP topology change notification bridge protocol unit received counter.

snIfRstpConfigBPDUTransmitted.name: snIfRstpConfigBPDUTransmitted
snIfRstpConfigBPDUTransmitted.description: RSTP configuration bridge protocol unit transmitted counter.

snIfRstpTCNBPDUTransmitted.name: snIfRstpTCNBPDUTransmitted
snIfRstpTCNBPDUTransmitted.description: RSTP topology change notification bridge protocol unit transmitted counter.

snTrunkTable.name: snTrunkTable
snTrunkTable.description: A specific snTrunkTable consists of a number of Trunk port-mask.

snTrunkEntry.name: snTrunkEntry
snTrunkEntry.description: An entry in the snTrunkTable indicates the configuration on a specified Trunk port membership.

snTrunkIndex.name: snTrunkIndex
snTrunkIndex.description: The number of the trunk entries can be configured. This can be 32*<slots> for Jetcore, and 16*<slots> for Ironcore.

snTrunkType.name: snTrunkType
snTrunkType.description: The trunk connection type which specifies what device the trunk ports are connected to.

snMSTrunkTable.name: snMSTrunkTable
snMSTrunkTable.description: A table contains the configuration of port members of multi-slot trunk groups.

snMSTrunkPortIndex.name: snMSTrunkPortIndex
snMSTrunkPortIndex.description: The primary port of a trunk group. For module with Gig ports, primary port is port 1, 3, 5, 7. For module with 10/100 ports, primary port is port 1, 5, 9, 13, 17, 21.

snMSTrunkPortList.name: snMSTrunkPortList
snMSTrunkPortList.description: A list of port indices which are the port membership of a trunk group. Each port index is a 16-bit integer in big endian order. The first port index must be the primary port index.

snMSTrunkType.name: snMSTrunkType
snMSTrunkType.description: The trunk connection type which specifies what device the trunk ports are connected to.

snMSTrunkRowStatus.name: snMSTrunkRowStatus
snMSTrunkRowStatus.description: To create or delete a table entry.

snMSTrunkIfTable.name: snMSTrunkIfTable
snMSTrunkIfTable.description: A table contains the configuration of port members of multi-slot trunk groups.

snMSTrunkIfIndex.name: snMSTrunkIfIndex
snMSTrunkIfIndex.description: The primary port(IfIndex) of a trunk group. For module with Gig ports, primary port is port 1, 3, 5, 7. For module with 10/100 ports, primary port is port 1, 5, 9, 13, 17, 21.

snMSTrunkIfList.name: snMSTrunkIfList
snMSTrunkIfList.description: A list of interface indices which are the port membership of a trunk group. Each interface index is a 16-bit integer in big endian order. The first interface/port index must be the primary port(ifIndex) index.

snMSTrunkIfType.name: snMSTrunkIfType
snMSTrunkIfType.description: The trunk connection type which specifies what device the trunk ports are connected to.

snMSTrunkIfRowStatus.name: snMSTrunkIfRowStatus
snMSTrunkIfRowStatus.description: To create or delete a table entry.

snSwSummaryMode.name: snSwSummaryMode
snSwSummaryMode.description: The Switch Group Configuration Summary is configured either enabled or disabled and the default is disabled mode. enabled(1)...........activate Switch Configuration Summary. disabled(0)..........no Switch Configuration Summary.

snDhcpGatewayListTable.name: snDhcpGatewayListTable
snDhcpGatewayListTable.description: A table of DHCP gateway list of addresses.

snDhcpGatewayListEntry.name: snDhcpGatewayListEntry
snDhcpGatewayListEntry.description: An entry in the IP Port Address table.

snDhcpGatewayListId.name: snDhcpGatewayListId
snDhcpGatewayListId.description: The ID for a DHCP gateway list entry.

snDhcpGatewayListAddrList.name: snDhcpGatewayListAddrList
snDhcpGatewayListAddrList.description: The DHCP gateway address list for each DHCP gateway list ID. This list contains 1 to 8 IP addresses represented by octet string.

snDhcpGatewayListRowStatus.name: snDhcpGatewayListRowStatus
snDhcpGatewayListRowStatus.description: This object is used to create and delete row in the table and control if they are used. The values that can be written are: delete(3)...deletes the row create(4)...creates a new row or modifies an exsisting row If the row exists, then a SET with value of create(4) returns error 'badValue'. Deleted rows go away immediately. The following values can be returned on reads: noSuch(0)...no such row other(1)....some other case valid(2)....the row exists and is valid

snDnsGatewayIpAddrList.name: snDnsGatewayIpAddrList
snDnsGatewayIpAddrList.description: The DNS Gateway IP address list. This list contains 4 IP addresses represented by octet string.

snMacFilterEntry.name: snMacFilterEntry
snMacFilterEntry.description: An entry in the MAC filter table.

snMacFilterIndex.name: snMacFilterIndex
snMacFilterIndex.description: The table index for a filter entry.

snMacFilterAction.name: snMacFilterAction
snMacFilterAction.description: Action to take if the Mac packet match with this filter.

snMacFilterFrameType.name: snMacFilterFrameType
snMacFilterFrameType.description: Frame Type: ethernet-type, LLC and SNAP types

snMacFilterRowStatus.name: snMacFilterRowStatus
snMacFilterRowStatus.description: This object is used to create and delete row in the table and control if they are used. The values that can be written are: delete(3)...deletes the row create(4)...creates a new row modify(5)...modifies an exsisting row If the row exists, then a SET with value of create(4) returns error 'badValue'. Deleted rows go away immediately. The following values can be returned on reads: noSuch(0)...no such row invalid(1)...Setting it to 'invalid' has the effect of rendering it inoperative.. valid(2)....the row exists and is valid

snMacFilterPortAccessEntry.name: snMacFilterPortAccessEntry
snMacFilterPortAccessEntry.description: An entry in the MAC Filter Port access table.

snMacFilterPortAccessPortIndex.name: snMacFilterPortAccessPortIndex
snMacFilterPortAccessPortIndex.description: The port index. For FastIron/NetIron products, port index value is from 1 to 42 For BigIron products, port index is an encoded number: The bit 0 to bit 7: port number. The bit 8 to bit 11: slot number. For virtual router interface, slot number is 15, port number is the virtual router port from 1 to 60. Therefore, port index value for BigIron is from 257 to 3900.

snMacFilterPortAccessFilters.name: snMacFilterPortAccessFilters
snMacFilterPortAccessFilters.description: 1st octet correspond to 1st filter number and so on.

snMacFilterPortAccessRowStatus.name: snMacFilterPortAccessRowStatus
snMacFilterPortAccessRowStatus.description: This object is used to create and delete row in the table and control if they are used. The values that can be written are: delete(3)...deletes the row create(4)...creates a new row If the row exists, then a SET with value of create(4) returns error 'badValue'. Deleted rows go away immediately. The following values can be returned on reads: noSuch(0)...no such row invalid(1)...Setting it to 'invalid' has the effect of rendering it inoperative.. valid(2)....the row exists and is valid

snMacFilterIfAccessEntry.name: snMacFilterIfAccessEntry
snMacFilterIfAccessEntry.description: An entry in the MAC Filter Port access table.

snMacFilterIfAccessFilters.name: snMacFilterIfAccessFilters
snMacFilterIfAccessFilters.description: 1st octet correspond to 1st filter number and so on.

snMacFilterIfAccessRowStatus.name: snMacFilterIfAccessRowStatus
snMacFilterIfAccessRowStatus.description: This object is used to create and delete row in the table and control if they are used. snNTPPollInterval.name: snNTPPollInterval
snNTPPollInterval.description: Interval specifies how often to poll the NTP server. Each unit is one second. This object is not supported in NI devices from R5.3

snNTPSummerTimeEnable.name: snNTPSummerTimeEnable
snNTPSummerTimeEnable.description: Enable/Disable daylight saving time. This enables daylight saving time for time/date starting 02:00:00 of first Sunday in April and ending 02:00:00 of last Sunday in October every year.

snNTPSystemClock.name: snNTPSystemClock
snNTPSystemClock.description: System clock, in the following format: octet 0: seconds after the minute [0-60] octet 1: minutes after the hour [0-59] octet 2: hours since midnight [0-23] octet 3: day of the month [1-31] octet 4: months since January [0-11] octet 5: years since 1900 octet 6: days since Sunday [0-6] Setting this object requires valid value in octets 0 to 5, and zero in octet 6. System clock can be disabled by setting zero to all octets.

snNTPSync.name: snNTPSync
snNTPSync.description: Initiate time synchronization to the NTP servers. For set operation, only 'synchronize(2)' is accepted. For get operation, always return 'other(1)'. This object is not supported in NI devices from R5.3

snNTPServerEntry.name: snNTPServerEntry
snNTPServerEntry.description: An entry in the NTP server table.

snNTPServerRowStatus.name: snNTPServerRowStatus
snNTPServerRowStatus.description: To create or delete a NTP server table entry.

snRadiusSNMPAccess.name: snRadiusSNMPAccess
snRadiusSNMPAccess.description: Indicate whether RADIUS server and key related MIB objects can be accessed by SNMP manager. If value is disabled, then snRadiusKey and snRadiusServerTable objects will not be accessible.

snRadiusRetransmit.name: snRadiusRetransmit
snRadiusRetransmit.description: The number of authentication query retransmissions to the Radius server.

snRadiusTimeOut.name: snRadiusTimeOut
snRadiusTimeOut.description: Interval specifies how long to wait for authentication reply from the Radius server, each unit is one second.

snRadiusDeadTime.name: snRadiusDeadTime
snRadiusDeadTime.description: Interval specifies Radius server dead time, each unit is one minute.

snRadiusKey.name: snRadiusKey
snRadiusKey.description: Authentication key displayed as encrypted text. Write operation can only be done if the SET request uses SNMPv3 with data encrypted using privacy key. FastIron and NetIron platforms support keysize upto 64 characters.

snRadiusLoginMethod.name: snRadiusLoginMethod
snRadiusLoginMethod.description: A sequence of authentication methods. Each octet represents a method to authenticate the user login process. Each octet has the following enumeration value: enable(1) - authenticate by command line interface enable password radius(2) - authenticate by requesting radius server local(3) - authenticate by local user account table line(4) - authenticate by telnet password tacplus(5) - authenticate by requesting tacplus server none(6) - do not authenticate tacacs(7) - authenticate by requesting tacacs server Setting a zero length octet string invalidates all previous authentication methods.

snRadiusEnableMethod.name: snRadiusEnableMethod
snRadiusEnableMethod.description: A sequence of authentication methods. Each octet represents a method to authenticate the user entering priviledge mode of the command line interface. Each octet has the following enumeration value: enable(1) - authenticate by command line interface enable password radius(2) - authenticate by requesting radius server local(3) - authenticate by local user account table line(4) - authenticate by telnet password tacplus(5) - authenticate by requesting tacplus server none(6) - do not authenticate tacacs(7) - authenticate by requesting tacacs server Setting a zero length octet string invalidates all previous authentication methods.

snRadiusWebServerMethod.name: snRadiusWebServerMethod
snRadiusWebServerMethod.description: A sequence of authentication methods. Each octet represents a method to authenticate the user accessing the web-server. Each octet has the following enumeration value: enable(1) - authenticate by command line interface enable password radius(2) - authenticate by requesting radius server local(3) - authenticate by local user account table line(4) - authenticate by telnet password tacplus(5) - authenticate by requesting tacplus server none(6) - do not authenticate tacacs(7) - authenticate by requesting tacacs server Setting a zero length octet string invalidates all previous authentication methods.

snRadiusSNMPServerMethod.name: snRadiusSNMPServerMethod
snRadiusSNMPServerMethod.description: A sequence of authentication methods. Each octet represents a method to authenticate the user accessing the snmp-server. Each octet has the following enumeration value: enable(1) - authenticate by command line interface enable password radius(2) - authenticate by requesting radius server local(3) - authenticate by local user account table line(4) - authenticate by telnet password tacplus(5) - authenticate by requesting tacplus server none(6) - do not authenticate tacacs(7) - authenticate by requesting tacacs server Setting a zero length octet string invalidates all previous authentication methods.

snRadiusServerEntry.name: snRadiusServerEntry
snRadiusServerEntry.description: An entry in the Radius server table.

snRadiusServerRowStatus.name: snRadiusServerRowStatus
snRadiusServerRowStatus.description: To create or delete a Radius server table entry.

snRadiusServerRowKey.name: snRadiusServerRowKey
snRadiusServerRowKey.description: Authentication key displayed as encrypted text. FastIron and NetIron platforms support keysize upto 64 characters.

snRadiusServerUsage.name: snRadiusServerUsage
snRadiusServerUsage.description: To allow this server to be dedicated for a particular AAA activity.

snTacacsRetransmit.name: snTacacsRetransmit
snTacacsRetransmit.description: The number of authentication query retransmissions to the Tacacs server.

snTacacsTimeOut.name: snTacacsTimeOut
snTacacsTimeOut.description: Interval specifies how long to wait for authentication reply from the Tacacs server, each unit is one second.

snTacacsDeadTime.name: snTacacsDeadTime
snTacacsDeadTime.description: Interval specifies Tacacs server dead time, each unit is one minute.

snTacacsKey.name: snTacacsKey
snTacacsKey.description: Authentication key displayed as encrypted text. Write operation can only be done if the SET request uses SNMPv3 with data encrypted using privacy key. FastIron and NetIron platforms support keysize upto 64 characters.

snTacacsSNMPAccess.name: snTacacsSNMPAccess
snTacacsSNMPAccess.description: Indicate whether TACACS+ server and key related MIB objects can be accessed by SNMP manager. If value is disabled, then snTacacsKey and snTacacsServerTable MIB objects will not be accessible.

snTacacsServerEntry.name: snTacacsServerEntry
snTacacsServerEntry.description: An entry in the Tacacs server table.

snTacacsServerRowStatus.name: snTacacsServerRowStatus
snTacacsServerRowStatus.description: To create or delete a Tacacs server table entry.

snTacacsServerRowKey.name: snTacacsServerRowKey
snTacacsServerRowKey.description: Authentication key displayed as encrypted text. Write operation can only be done if the SET request uses SNMPv3 with data encrypted using privacy key. FastIron and NetIron platforms support keysize upto 64 characters.

snTacacsServerUsage.name: snTacacsServerUsage
snTacacsServerUsage.description: To allow this server to be dedicated for a particular AAA activity.

snQosProfileTable.name: snQosProfileTable
snQosProfileTable.description: A table contains the configuration of qos profile groups.

snQosProfileIndex.name: snQosProfileIndex
snQosProfileIndex.description: The table index of QOS Profile.

snQosBindTable.name: snQosBindTable
snQosBindTable.description: A table contains the configuration of 802.1p to qos profile binding groups.

snQosBindIndex.name: snQosBindIndex
snQosBindIndex.description: The table index of QOS Bind.

snQosBindProfileIndex.name: snQosBindProfileIndex
snQosBindProfileIndex.description: QOS Bind Profile Index. This is pointer to the index of snQosProfile Table.

snDosAttackPortTable.name: snDosAttackPortTable
snDosAttackPortTable.description: Denial of service attack port table.

snDosAttackPortEntry.name: snDosAttackPortEntry
snDosAttackPortEntry.description: An entry of the denial of service attack port table.

snAuthorizationCommandMethods.name: snAuthorizationCommandMethods
snAuthorizationCommandMethods.description: A sequence of authorization methods. Each octet represents a method to authorize the user command. Each octet has the following value: radius(2) - authorize by requesting radius server tacplus(5) - authorize by requesting tacplus server none(6) - skip authorization Setting a zero length octet string invalidates all previous authorization methods.

snAuthorizationCommandLevel.name: snAuthorizationCommandLevel
snAuthorizationCommandLevel.description: Commands, which are equal to and less than the specified command level here needs to be authorized. Possible enumeration values: 0 - Privilege level 0 4 - Privilege level 4 5 - Privilege level 5.

snAuthorizationExec.name: snAuthorizationExec
snAuthorizationExec.description: A sequence of exec authorization methods. Each octet represents a method for telnet or SSH login authorization. Each octet has the following enumeration value: radius(2) - send exec authorization request to radius server tacplus(5) - send exec authorization request to tacplus server none(6) - no exec authorization Setting a zero length octet string invalidates all authorization methods.

snAccountingCommandMethods.name: snAccountingCommandMethods
snAccountingCommandMethods.description: A sequence of accounting methods. Each octet represents a method to account for the user command. Each octet has the following enumeration value: radius(2) - send accounting info to radius server tacplus(5) - send accounting info to tacplus server none(6) - skip accounting Setting a zero length octet string invalidates all previous accounting methods.

snAccountingCommandLevel.name: snAccountingCommandLevel
snAccountingCommandLevel.description: Commands, which are equal to and less than the specified command level here will be accounted. Possible enumeration values: level0 - Privilege level 0 level4 - Privilege level 4 level5 - Privilege level 5.

snAccountingExec.name: snAccountingExec
snAccountingExec.description: A sequence of accounting methods. Each octet represents a method for telnet or SSH login accounting. Each octet has the following enumeration value: radius(2) - send accounting info to radius server tacplus(5) - send accounting info to tacplus server none(6) - skip accounting Setting a zero length octet string invalidates all previous accounting methods.

snAccountingSystem.name: snAccountingSystem
snAccountingSystem.description: A sequence of accounting methods. Each octet represents a method to account for the system related events. Each octet has the following enumeration value: radius(2) - send accounting info to radius server tacplus(5) - send accounting info to tacplus server none(6) - skip accounting Setting a zero length octet string invalidates all previous accounting methods.

snNetFlowGblProtocolDisable.name: snNetFlowGblProtocolDisable
snNetFlowGblProtocolDisable.description: bit 0 - other, disable all protocols export except UDP and TCP bit 1 - tcp, disable TCP protocol export bit 2 - udp, disable UDP protocol export

snNetFlowGblActiveTimeout.name: snNetFlowGblActiveTimeout
snNetFlowGblActiveTimeout.description: Maximum time an active flow can be in the NetFlow cache (minutes: 1..60)

snNetFlowGblInactiveTimeout.name: snNetFlowGblInactiveTimeout
snNetFlowGblInactiveTimeout.description: Maximum time an inactive flow can be in the NetFlow cache (seconds: 10..600)

snNetFlowCollectorTable.name: snNetFlowCollectorTable
snNetFlowCollectorTable.description: A table of each NetFlow collector information.

snNetFlowCollectorEntry.name: snNetFlowCollectorEntry
snNetFlowCollectorEntry.description: A row in the NetFlow collector table.

snNetFlowCollectorIndex.name: snNetFlowCollectorIndex
snNetFlowCollectorIndex.description: The index to the NetFlow collector table.

snNetFlowCollectorUdpPort.name: snNetFlowCollectorUdpPort
snNetFlowCollectorUdpPort.description: The NetFlow collector UDP port number.

snNetFlowCollectorSourceInterface.name: snNetFlowCollectorSourceInterface
snNetFlowCollectorSourceInterface.description: The ifIndex value to specify source port to export NetFlow packet. Value 0 to indicate default outgoing port.

snNetFlowCollectorRowStatus.name: snNetFlowCollectorRowStatus
snNetFlowCollectorRowStatus.description: To create or delete a NetFlow collector table entry.

snNetFlowAggregationTable.name: snNetFlowAggregationTable
snNetFlowAggregationTable.description: A table of each NetFlow aggregation scheme information.

snNetFlowAggregationEntry.name: snNetFlowAggregationEntry
snNetFlowAggregationEntry.description: A row in the NetFlow Aggregation table.

snNetFlowAggregationIp.name: snNetFlowAggregationIp
snNetFlowAggregationIp.description: The NetFlow aggregation collector ip address.

snNetFlowAggregationUdpPort.name: snNetFlowAggregationUdpPort
snNetFlowAggregationUdpPort.description: The NetFlow aggregation collector UDP port number.

snNetFlowAggregationSourceInterface.name: snNetFlowAggregationSourceInterface
snNetFlowAggregationSourceInterface.description: The ifIndex value to specify source port to export NetFlow aggregation packet. Value 0 to indicate default outgoing port.

snNetFlowAggregationNumberOfCacheEntries.name: snNetFlowAggregationNumberOfCacheEntries
snNetFlowAggregationNumberOfCacheEntries.description: Number of cache entries for aggregation scheme

snNetFlowAggregationActiveTimeout.name: snNetFlowAggregationActiveTimeout
snNetFlowAggregationActiveTimeout.description: Maximum time an active flow can be in the aggregation cache

snNetFlowAggregationInactiveTimeout.name: snNetFlowAggregationInactiveTimeout
snNetFlowAggregationInactiveTimeout.description: Maximum time an inactive flow can be in the aggregation cache

snNetFlowAggregationEnable.name: snNetFlowAggregationEnable
snNetFlowAggregationEnable.description: Enable/disable NetFlow aggregation for this aggregation scheme.

snNetFlowAggregationRowStatus.name: snNetFlowAggregationRowStatus
snNetFlowAggregationRowStatus.description: To create or delete a NetFlow collector table entry.

snNetFlowIfTable.name: snNetFlowIfTable
snNetFlowIfTable.description: A list of interface entries. The number of entries is given by the value of ifNumber.

snNetFlowIfEntry.name: snNetFlowIfEntry
snNetFlowIfEntry.description: Entry containing the type of switching performed on that interface.

snNetFlowIfIndex.name: snNetFlowIfIndex
snNetFlowIfIndex.description: A unique value, greater than zero, for each interface. It is recommended that values are assigned contiguously starting from 1. The value for each interface sub-layer must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re-initialization.

snNetFlowIfFlowSwitching.name: snNetFlowIfFlowSwitching
